text: Alexeyevka () is a rural locality (a village) in Kozhay-Semyonovsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 44 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 14 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki, 8 km from Kozhay-Semyonovka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Alexeyevka, Miyakinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
